+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S4-P01-T041 (resumable 2016+ backfill planner + cursor; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Forty-first task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S4 (2016+ A0/A1/A2 Expansion -- historical backfill and regional expansion). Goal: split the 2016+ history backfill into small monthly shards that are retryable and resumable. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a planner and cursor semantics, not wired to real backfill fetching. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/backfill_planner.py (plan_shards producing monthly shards backfill/YYYY-MM, a ShardCursor with status, last_confirmed_id, processed, and total, a process_shard that resumes past the last confirmed id, is idempotent by the content-addressed id, and checkpoints only after an item is confirmed applied, a resume path, and the CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA), schemas/backfill_checkpoint.sql (cn_backfill_shards with the shard primary key, status, last_confirmed_id, and counts plus a status index), BACKFILL_PLANNER_SPEC.md, and evidence/ADP-S4-P01-T041/backfill_plan.json. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P01-T041/test-results/backfill_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the planner produces 127 monthly shards from backfill/2016-01 to backfill/2026-07; running the same shard three times produces no duplicates, since the first run applies all 10 items and the second and third apply 0, leaving the applied set at 10 unique ids; and an interrupted shard resumes from its last confirmed checkpoint, since interrupting after 4 items leaves the shard in_progress with a checkpoint and the resume applies exactly the remaining 6 to reach done with 10 total and no redo, skip, or duplicate, starting strictly after the checkpoint. This is the execution foundation for the 2016+ recoverable-history constraint. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S3-P03-T040 (Board 3 official-view A0 canary + reversible switch; CANARY)
 
 - Fortieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the last of S3-P03. After the Owner S3 Exit gate approved A0 promotion, implemented a reversible Board 3 official-view canary. release_mode CANARY. Change to deploy/cloudflare/worker_cloud.js: a feature flag BOARD3_A0_ONLY (default OFF), an a0Board3Eligible gate that admits only a central .gov.cn or A0-whitelisted source as Board 3 evidence and demotes media to discovery when the flag is on, applied in selectDaily, and a non-destructive GET /api/a0-canary endpoint that fetches the real gov.cn policy listing (one subrequest) and reports what Board 3 would look like under the A0 gate without writing anything to production. Deployed adp-cloud version 5bcd9f21 (build b189d3cc0703, self-excluding hash 9cd3d8a2fe68 -> b189d3cc0703). Acceptance verified live (evidence/ADP-S3-P03-T040/{canary_live_response.json, test-results/deploy_verify.txt}): the official evidence rate is 100% -- /api/a0-canary found 8 real gov.cn policy originals (e.g. 中华人民共和国政府信息公开条例, 国务院办公厅通知), all A0-eligible, with the media evidence rate under the gate at 0 and the 105 current board3 media items demoted to discovery -- and a P0 regression rolls back in one deploy by setting BOARD3_A0_ONLY=false (currently that state) or wrangler versions deploy 64c8b842. Because the flag ships OFF, production Board 3 (media) and the six themes are unchanged: both adp.linzezhang.com and adp-cloud.linzezhang35.workers.dev show 6/6 themes (cosmos/forest/fresh/minimal/techno/warm), hero videos, and all 8 routes 200. The full flip to official-as-default is deliberately deferred pending the A0 adapters wired to the worker cron (DIR-007 budgeted) plus the real 14-day shadow. PARAM-ADP-1124 re-attested unchanged (59.6) as adp-v03-j5-cloud-v14; TRACEABILITY_MATRIX / VERSION_MATRIX / delivery_tasks / deployment manifest updated. Cost: 1 canary subrequest per manual call, D1 read 105, cron path unchanged (0 new subrequests, flag OFF), ~$0 recurring. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
